<br>
Just what I've read.<br>
<br>
As far as <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> current</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> xp bonuses and penalties, the race xp penalties and bonuses still exist. The following list is correct for races.<br>
<br>
Halfling - 95%<br>
barb 105%<br>
ogre - 115%<br>
troll, iksar - 120%<br>
vah shir - no clue <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
all others - 100%<br>
<br>
The class penalties were worked around by changing the amount of xp recieved by class, but class <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> bonuses</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> were not. A class that had a penalty previously doesn't really have one now becuase the way xp is awarded was changed. Here is the list of class xp modifiers.<br>
<br>
Bard, paladin, ranger, SK - 140%<br>
monk - 120%<br>
Int casters - 110%<br>
wis casters 100%<br>
warrior, rogue - 90%<br>
beastlord - no clue<br>
<br>
The way they removed a class xp penalty was to increase the amount of xp recieved to match the penalty. A paladin had a class penalty of 40%. Now paladins get 40% more xp per kill to compensate, essentially eliminating the class penalty. They did <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> not</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> remove the class bonus to warriors and rogues. A warrior or rogue will level 10% faster than another class of the same race. <br>
<br>
